processDocumentation.technologyDescription:
Typical composition of sources of postconsumer material arriving at material recycling facilities (MRFs); MRF technology levels for non-fiber lines were separated into 4 categories and statistics were used to estimate the percentage of plastic handled under each category:
• Level 1 – manual separation only, with conveyor or balers;
• Level 2 – use of conveyor, baler, and magnetic separator;
• Level 3 – in addition to level 2 equipment, the use of other separator technology such as eddy current, air classifier, trommels, and screens, or an integrated sort system;
• Level 4 – the addition of computer-assisted technology, i.e., scanners.
